Case 1:20-cr-00330-AJN Document 765 Filed 08/10/22 Page 50 of 95 2788 LCI1MAX1
1 MR. EVERDELL: Slightly different. That would be "an individual under the age of 18," because that's the substantive count.
2 THE COURT: Yes. Line 3, replacing "minors" with "an --" wait. Let me just read that sentence again.
3 MR. ROHRBACH: I think these are all references to the conspiracy.
4 MR. EVERDELL: That's right. I'm sorry, your Honor. This is still talking about the conspiracy. So that one on line 3 would still be "sex trafficking of individuals under the age of 18."
5 THE COURT: Yes. I agree with that. Okay. So for all of Instruction 34, all of the instances -- well, in the second paragraph -- no, I'm sorry. I won't repeat it. We got it. Page 45, line 3, "individuals under the age of 18."
6 Okey dokey. Next.
7 MR. EVERDELL: So, your Honor, now we have page 49, or instruction No. 36. It's --
8 THE COURT: I'm sorry. What page? 49?
9 MR. EVERDELL: Page 49, Instruction 36.
10 THE COURT: Okay. Actually, before you start, I'll just note, there's an extra word, "Two," T-W-O, in the title. So line 1, it's just Counts One, Three, and Five, deleting the word "Two."
11 SOUTHERN DISTRICT REPORTERS, P.C. (212) 805-0300
